HEADWORD: Ortive
<hw>Or"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ortivus</ets>, fr. <ets>oriri</ets>, <ets>ortus</ets>, to rise: cf.
F. <ets>ortive</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or relating to the time or act of
rising; eastern; <as>as, the <ex>ortive</ex> amplitude of a
planet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
